cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep network architecture for image denoising, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The network is trained discriminatively in an end-to-end fashion, which involves optimizing a loss function (cs.LG). The network uses a Gaussian Conditional Random Field (GCRF) model, which is a probabilistic graphical model (cs.AI). The network is evaluated on image datasets, which involves processing and analyzing multimedia data (cs.MM). Finally, the network is trained using a peak signal-to-noise ratio measure, which is a common metric used in neural network optimization (cs.NE).
